The paper discusses a method for improving performance on classification tasks through sparsity in representations. This is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on autoencoders, which are a type of neural network, and discusses their effectiveness compared to other methods such as dropout and RBMs. This suggests that the paper could also fall under the categories of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) and "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the MNIST and NORB datasets, which are commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
